    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Relatively narrow inclined bands of masonry found on walls of some northern Mesoamerican architecture since about 800 BCE; after around 300 CE often part of the talud-tablero architectural feature.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Wordt gebruikt voor relatief smalle schuingezette banden metselwerk die vanaf 800 v.C. soms worden gevonden op muren van Midden-Amerikaanse bouwwerken. Na ongeveer 300 v.C. zijn ze vaak onderdeel van het architectonische element talud-tablero.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>大約西元前800年的中美洲北部，建築牆面所採用之較窄的傾斜石砌飾帶。約於西元300年以後，多成為神廟建築形式的特色之一。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
